    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;HTTP Origin-Bound Authentication (HOBA) is a digital-signature-based design for an HTTP authentication method.  The design can also be used in JavaScript-based authentication embedded in HTML.  HOBA is an alternative to HTTP authentication schemes that require passwords and therefore avoids all problems related to passwords, such as leakage of server-side password databases.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
